		<label>treeslurper</label>
		<description>Treeslurpers are descendents of bio-engineered elephants, bred to consume living trees and plants for the purpose of clearing land for construction. They are approximately the size of a small bear. As their name suggests, their favorite food is trees of any kind. Once they escaped containment, they became an invasive species. If you encounter wild Treeslurpers, be sure to kill them or tame them before they destroy the arboreal ecoystem.</description>
